<div><ol>
<li>Apply to *BYU-Idaho&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.besmart.com/" target="_blank">www.besmart.com</a>. Please contact Admissions at (208) 496-1300 for assistance or answers to your questions regarding the university application process or besmart.com. Choose either the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.besmart.com/" target="_self">On-campus Application</a> or&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.besmart.com/">Online Degree Application</a> </li>
<li>Complete the *background check at <a href="http://www.certifiedbackground.com" target="_blank">www.certifiedbackground.com</a> and click on "Students." In the Package Code box, enter the package code listed below.             
<ul>
<li>If you are 20 years or younger your code is: RG85</li>
<li>If you are 21 years or older your code is: RG85-21</li>
<li>Only background checks from certifiedbackground.com will be accepted.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Submit your RN to BSN Application to Nursing Outreach, BYU-Idaho, 103 ASB, Rexburg, ID 83460-8011.&nbsp;Choose either the application for&nbsp;<a href="Documents/nursing/nursing/RN-BSN/RNtoBSNApplicationAlumni-6-2012.pdf">BYU-Idaho ASN Alumni</a> or&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href="Documents/nursing/nursing/RN-BSN/RNtoBSNApplicationTransfer-6-2012.pdf">Application for Transfer Students</a></li>
</ol>
<p>*NOTE: BYU-I ASN graduates whose background check was done prior to Fall 2012 <em>must</em> complete a new background check through CertifiedBackground; the ASN background done prior to Fall 2012 is not sufficiently comprehensive for the BSN Program.</p>
<ol> </ol>
<h3>Selection Priority</h3>
<p>Although not guaranteed, the Department of Nursing strives to admit about 60 applicants (40 Full-time and 20 Part-time) each semester. Applicants are admitted in the following priority:</p>
<ol>
<li>Ricks College/BYU-Idaho ASN graduates</li>
<li>ASN graduates from other Colleges or Universities</li>
</ol>
<p>* If you wish to take University course or non-nursing course requirements prior to acceptance into the RN to BSN Program, apply as an online, Continuing Education&nbsp;or Part-time student.</p>
